docs.abstract: The tech giants singled out booming results from their devices in their quarterly financial results.
docs.snippet: The tech giants singled out booming results from their devices in their quarterly financial results.
docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — For Apple and Amazon, the holidays are the time to shine, the period when shoppers have the greatest appetite to buy their devices and, in Amazon’s case, anything else that can be stuffed into a box and delivered to homes.

headline.main: Amazon and Apple Gush Over Holiday Sales
headline.print_headline: Amazon and Apple Holiday Sales Yield a Happy New Year

byline.original: By Nick Wingfield and Brian X. Chen

docs.abstract: Next to Apple’s iOS and Google’s Android, Amazon’s voice assistant may be turning into the third great consumer computing platform of our era.
docs.snippet: Next to Apple’s iOS and Google’s Android, Amazon’s voice assistant may be turning into the third great consumer computing platform of our era.
docs.lead_paragraph: My wife and I were just settling into bed one night when Alexa, the other woman in my life, decided to make herself heard.

headline.main: Why We May Soon Be Living in Alexa’s World
headline.print_headline: Alexa Will Be Everywhere. We’d Better Get Used to It.

docs.abstract: The employees of Amazon, Berkshire Hathaway and JPMorgan Chase may benefit from a new insurance scheme. But the rest of us could suffer.
docs.snippet: The employees of Amazon, Berkshire Hathaway and JPMorgan Chase may benefit from a new insurance scheme. But the rest of us could suffer.
docs.lead_paragraph: Here’s the good news about the announcement this week that Amazon, Berkshire Hathaway and JPMorgan Chase are forming a new company to cover health care for their employees: If you’re one of the million-plus people who work at these companies, or a family member of one, you’re likely to get cheaper, better health care pretty soon.

headline.main: A Good Health Care Deal, but Only for Some
headline.print_headline: A Good Deal, but Only for Some

docs.abstract: This year’s Oscar nominees feature a terrific array of talent whose work is nearly infinitely available to sample on streaming video.
docs.snippet: This year’s Oscar nominees feature a terrific array of talent whose work is nearly infinitely available to sample on streaming video.
docs.lead_paragraph: The range of films nominated for the 90th Academy Awards seems wider than average, and that’s gratifying. There are the nominations that move the needle a little in terms of making the American film industry less white-male dominated.

headline.print_headline: Don’t Take Your Eyes Off the Nominees

docs.abstract: It can be tempting to hook up everything you love to the internet. But take a moment to appreciate some of the objects that can remain unplugged.
docs.snippet: It can be tempting to hook up everything you love to the internet. But take a moment to appreciate some of the objects that can remain unplugged.
docs.lead_paragraph: It still feels magical to light up your living room by saying “Alexa, turn on the lights.” But with all the hype surrounding so-called smart things — everyday devices that are connected to the internet — it’s easy to forget that sometimes the dumb stuff is just better.

headline.main: In an Era of ‘Smart’ Things, Sometimes Dumb Stuff Is Better
headline.print_headline: In ‘Smart’ Things Era, Sometimes Dumb Is Better

docs.abstract: Everyone likes to complain about our company-based system, but there have been real examples of innovation.
docs.snippet: Everyone likes to complain about our company-based system, but there have been real examples of innovation.
docs.lead_paragraph: In the United States, most working-age people get their health insurance through work. It’s a weird, kludgy system, largely an artifact of history. Economists, politicians and workers alike complain that the setup is inefficient and maddening.

headline.main: Employer Health Insurance: Often-Hated, Sometimes Pioneering, and Now on Amazon’s Radar
headline.print_headline: Employer Health System: Flawed, but Innovative
